<subSubSection id="8C8E6575FFCC6A73FF8994C41A70B802" pageId="55" pageNumber="813" type="conservation">
<paragraph id="C42B36FEFFCC6A73FF8994C41A70B802" blockId="55.[115,1323,271,940]" pageId="55" pageNumber="813">
<emphasis id="F6E0EAECFFCC6A73FF8994C41FD0B988" bold="true" box="[117,464,669,698]" pageId="55" pageNumber="813">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
Classified as Data Deficient on The IUCN Red List (as 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFCC6A73FB4894C41F0CB9D3" baseAuthorityName="Peters" baseAuthorityYear="1866" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Falsistrellus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="55" pageNumber="813" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="mordax">Falsistrellus mordax</taxonomicName>
), as range, population abundance, and ecology are little known. Threats are not known. It is not known if the species is present in any protected areas. Further studies are needed into its distribution, abundance, ecology, and threats.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
